'''107.9 ABC Ballarat''', callsign '''3CRR''', is an [[ABC Local Radio]] station in [[Ballarat, Victoria]]. ABC Ballarat is one of the newest stations in the network, opened on June 30, 2003.<ref name="aboutus">{{cite web |title=About Us - ABC Ballarat |url=http://www.abc.net.au/ballarat/about.htm |date=2006-09-22 |accessdate=2007-12-04 |publisher=[[ABC Online]] |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20071028120753/http://www.abc.net.au/ballarat/about.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-10-28}}</ref> The station is the largest regional ABC station in [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] and serves Ballarat, [[Ararat, Victoria|Ararat]] and [[Daylesford, Victoria|Daylesford]], as well as parts of south-west Victoria including [[Hamilton, Victoria|Hamilton]], [[Port Fairy, Victoria|Port Fairy]], and [[Warrnambool, Victoria|Warrnambool]] through [[ABC South West Victoria]].<ref name="aboutus" />

A local breakfast program is presented by Dominic Brine from 6.00am to 7.45am, in addition to a south-west Victorian morning program hosted by Steve Martin between 8.30am and 11.00am.<ref name="aboutus" /> Two journalists work at the station producing content for both ABC Ballarat and ABC South West Victoria.<ref name="aboutus" /> The regional Statewide Drive program (3 - 6 PM) is also broadcast from the Ballarat studios. It is presented by Kathy Bedford and covers Victoria, southern New South Wales and a small part of eastern South Australia. It does not broadcast into the Melbourne metro area.

